## Resource Model

| Resource | Key | Operations |
|----------|-----|-----------|
| Group | GroupName/ARN | Create, Get, List, Update, Delete |
| SamplingRule | RuleName | Create, Get, List, Update, Delete |
| Trace | TraceId | BatchGet, GetSummaries, GetGraph, PutSegments |
| TraceRetrieval | RetrievalToken | Start, Get, List, Cancel |
| Insight | InsightId | Get, GetSummaries, GetEvents, GetImpactGraph |
| ResourcePolicy | PolicyName | Put, List, Delete |
| EncryptionConfig | (singleton) | Get, Put |
| IndexingRule | RuleName | Get, Update |
| TraceSegmentDestination | (singleton) | Get, Update |
| TelemetryRecords | (batch) | Put |

## Protocol

X-Ray uses the REST-JSON protocol (AWS `rest-json`). All operations are HTTP POST
except where documented. The service endpoint prefix is `xray`.

## Design Philosophy

For TotalStack emulation, X-Ray is a **store-driven** service:
1. All state is held in in-memory stores (XrayStore)
2. Generated handlers validate input per AWS docs
3. Store operations are pure CRUD — no delegation to external backends
4. Trace retrieval is emulated as immediate (no async polling needed in emulator)
5. Sampling decisions are emulated as deterministic from stored rules

